            "answer_text": "It may be easier than you\u2019d imagine. I do it all the time. Follow these steps: Clean your room and find an excellent place to work.Delete all your social media. If you can, sell your smartphone and use a simple phone. Make sure you are not reading any news either. These things stay in your subconscious and decrease your ability to concentrate and focus.Wake up no later than 6am, go to sleep no later than 10pm.When you wake up, eat a low-sugar breakfast that is full of carbohydrates. Make it quick, because you don\u2019t have a lot of time.Do not listen to anything other than classical music when working\u2014or better yet, pure silence.Walk around for 10 minutes while focusing on nothing but the act of walking. This refreshes and empties your mind, readying you for work.Work for an hour, then walk for ten minutes, focusing on nothing but walking in order to clear your mind.Eat a small snack often during your breaks.Download apps that speeds up video lectures and practice listening to audiobooks at extremely high speeds. After a few months of practice, you\u2019ll be able to digest close to 20 hours of material in a a normal day.Find at least four hours to completely relax in the evening. Make sure you do not become mindless though. Watching mindless TV shows will dull your mental capacity and incapacitate your work efficiency.Don\u2019t look at any screens an hour before you go to sleep.There may be a few more points, but these will really help. You\u2019ll be able to master the material for any four-year degree easily in the span of a few months if you remain diligent. Remember, above all, do not fill your mind with things that remain in your subconscious and distract you continually\u2014social media, news, newspapers, TV shows, etc. Empty your mind constantly and keep it sharp and fresh. ",
